Greek authorities say about 85 migrants have been rescued from a crippled boat in the Mediterranean Sea off the country&#8217;s southern coast. JOHANNESBURG - Greek authorities say about 85 migrants have been rescued from a crippled boat in the Mediterranean Sea off the country s southern coast. The wooden boat was drifting about 40 kilometres south-west of the southern port of Kalamata.There s no immediate information about the health of the passengers or where they were travelling to.(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)